fields.description:
This issue was found during investigations for 3.4 (see EUCA-6333)

When using the stopped STOPPED state to move ENABLED services between systems in an HA setup:

When using the stopped STOPPED state to move ENABLED services:

{code}
# euca-modify-service -s STOPPED SC_17 ; euca-modify-service -s ENABLED SC_175 ; euca-modify-service -s DISABLED SC_17
{code}

I got this error on modifying SC_17 to DISABLED:

{code}
# euca-modify-service -s DISABLED SC_17
Error(400 Bad Request): java.util.concurrent.ExecutionException: java.lang.RuntimeException: com.eucalyptus.ws.EucalyptusRemoteFault: Action:ProblemAction Code:soapenv:Client Id:RelatesTo Error: java.util.concurrent.ExecutionException: com.google.common.util.concurrent.UncheckedExecutionException: com.google.common.collect.ComputationException: com.eucalyptus.util.EucalyptusCloudException: Unable to run command: Task java.util.concurrent.FutureTask@5accdd55 rejected from java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor@54b327d[Terminated, pool size = 0, active threads = 0, queued tasks = 0, completed tasks = 2468]java.util.concurrent.ExecutionException: com.google.common.util.concurrent.UncheckedExecutionException: com.google.common.collect.ComputationException: com.eucalyptus.util.EucalyptusCloudException: Unable to run command: Task java.util.concurrent.FutureTask@5accdd55 rejected from java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor@54b327d[Terminated, pool size = 0, active threads = 0, queued tasks = 0, completed tasks = 2468]
{code}

and then was not able to perform any modifications for that service.

The configuration for the above test was:

{code}
machine00	CENTOS	6.4	64	REPO	[CLC WS CC00 SC00]
machine01	CENTOS	6.4	64	REPO	[CLC WS CC00 SC00]
machine02	CENTOS	6.4	64	REPO	[NC00]
{code}

Where 10.111.1.175 is machine00 and 10.111.5.17 is machine01.

comments.body:
This issue is not specific to HA, to reproduce you can use:

{code}
# euca-modify-service -s STOPPED SC_17
# euca-modify-service -s DISABLED SC_17
{code}
